<h1>Jason Zook</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://jasondoesstuff.com/now/">jasondoesstuff.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
San Diego
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Chief T-Shirt Wearer at IWearYourShirt.com (retired).  Last Name Pimp at BuyMyLastName.com (retired).  Author of Creativity For Sale.  Co-Founder of Teachery.co.  Co-Founder of Bumpsale.co.  Director of Action Taking at JasonDoesStuff.com.  Seller of Future at BuyMyFuture.com.  Fearless Entrepreneur.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help entrepreneurs take action in their lives and businesses.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Through product creation, writing, and self-guineau-pigging, I help people learn from my experiences to build lives and businesses that feel congruent to who they are at their core.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
You don’t get what you don’t ask for.  It's weird to live in a culture so obsessed with becoming successful quickly when no one who is successful got there quickly.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
The Obstacle is the Way, by Ryan Holiday.  ReWork, by Jason Fried and David Heinemeier Hansson.
</p>

